#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:1
msgid "Merge and review policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:3
msgid ""
"Our policy for merging and reviewing describes how we review one "
"another's work, and when we allow others to merge changes into our main "
"codebase. It tries to balance a few goals:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:6
msgid ""
"Iterate on PRs and merge them relatively quickly, so that we reduce the "
"debt associated with long-lasting PRs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:7
msgid ""
"Give enough time for others to provide their input and guide the PR "
"itself, and to ensure that we aren't creating a problem with the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:8
msgid ""
"Value iterative improvement over creating the perfect Pull Request, so "
"that we do not burden contributors with cumbersome discussion and minor "
"revision requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:9
msgid ""
"Recognize that we all have limited time and resources, and so cannot "
"guarantee a full quality assurance process each time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:10
msgid ""
"Give general preference to the opinions of maintainers of projects in the"
" PyData ecosystem, as a key stakeholder community of this theme."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:12
msgid "We follow these guidelines to achieve these goals:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:14
msgid ""
"Assume that all maintainers are acting in good faith and will use their "
"best judgment to make decisions in the best interests of the repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:15
msgid ""
"We can and will make mistakes, so encourage best practices in testing and"
" documentation to guard against this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:16
msgid ""
"It's important to share information, so give your best effort at telling "
"others about the work that you're doing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:17
msgid ""
"It's best to discuss and agree on important decisions at a high level "
"before implementation, so give the best effort at providing time and "
"invitation for others to provide feedback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:19
msgid "Policy for moderate changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:21
msgid ""
"These are changes that make modest changes to new or existing "
"functionality, but that aren't going to significantly change the default "
"behavior of the theme, user configuration, etc. This is the majority of "
"changes that we make."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:24
msgid "PRs should:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:26
msgid ""
"Refer to (and ideally close) an issue that describes the problem this "
"change is solving."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:27
msgid "Have relevant testing and documentation coverage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:29
msgid ""
"They can be merged when the above conditions are met, and one of these "
"things happens:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:31
msgid ""
"The PR has at least one approval from a core maintainer that isn't the PR"
" author"
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:32
msgid ""
"The PR author has signaled their intent to merge unless there are "
"objections, and 48 hours have passed since that comment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:34
msgid "Policy for major new features and breaking changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:36
msgid ""
"These are changes that significantly alter the experience of the user, or"
" that add significant complexity to the codebase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:38
msgid ""
"All the above, but PRs **must** have approval from at least one other "
"core maintainer before merging. In addition, the PR author should put "
"extra effort into ensuring that the relevant stakeholders are notified "
"about a change, so they can gauge its impact and provide feedback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:41
msgid "Policy For minor changes and bugfixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:43
msgid ""
"These are small changes that might be noticeable to the user, but in a "
"way that is clearly an improvement. They generally shouldn't touch too "
"many lines of code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../community/practices/merge.md:46
msgid ""
"Update the relevant tests and documentation, but PR authors are welcome "
"to self-merge whenever they like without PR approval."
msgstr ""

